message.content:
Analysis of the Target Image
--------------------------------
There are actually two separate “tower‐like” builds in the scene.

■ Left Build (8 total blocks, arranged in roughly five vertical layers):
1) Bottom Layer: Two vertical blue blocks serving as “legs.”  
2) Second Layer: One long yellow rectangular block bridging across those two legs.  
3) Third Layer: Two upright blocks side‐by‐side on top of the yellow block (blue on the left, red on the right).  
4) Fourth Layer: One horizontal green block spanning across the two upright blocks.  
5) Top Layer (Roof): Two orange wedges meeting in the middle to form a pitched roof.

■ Right Build (6 total blocks, arranged in five vertical layers):
1) Bottom Layer: Two orange cylinders lying next to each other (forming “wheels”).  
2) Second Layer: One horizontal green block bridging across the two cylinders.  
3) Third Layer: One red block placed on top of the green.  
4) Fourth Layer: One blue block on top of the red.  
5) Top Layer (Roof): A single orange wedge set front‐to‐back.

Dictionary Blocks Required
--------------------------------
Below are the exact block‐index selections (with no further rotation allowed) that match color, shape, and orientation:

• Blue cube/block (#1) – used 4 times  
• Red cube/block (#3) – used 2 times  
• Green rectangular block, horizontal orientation (#6) – used 2 times  
• Yellow rectangular block, horizontal orientation (#9) – used 1 time  
• Orange cylinder (#11) – used 2 times  
• Orange roof wedge, left‐right slope (#14) – used 1 time  
• Orange roof wedge, front‐to‐back slope (#15) – used 1 time  
• Orange roof wedge, mirrored left‐right slope (#16) – used 1 time  

Assembly Order
--------------------------------
Below is a possible step‐by‐step assembly sequence (for both builds combined). Use the block indices exactly as shown:

{
  Step1: Move block with index 1      // Left build, left blue leg
  Step2: Move block with index 1      // Left build, right blue leg
  Step3: Move block with index 9      // Yellow bridging block (left build)
  Step4: Move block with index 1      // Blue upright above the yellow (left build)
  Step5: Move block with index 3      // Red upright above the yellow (left build)
  Step6: Move block with index 6      // Green horizontal band (left build)
  Step7: Move block with index 14     // Left roof wedge (left build)
  Step8: Move block with index 16     // Right roof wedge (left build)
  Step9: Move block with index 11     // Right build, left orange cylinder
  Step10: Move block with index 11    // Right build, right orange cylinder
  Step11: Move block with index 6     // Right build, green block bridging cylinders
  Step12: Move block with index 3     // Red block on top (right build)
  Step13: Move block with index 1     // Blue block above red (right build)
  Step14: Move block with index 15    // Orange wedge roof (right build)
}
